# {{.Name}}

This project was scaffolded by `de project init`. It ships a working CRUD service
(webhook endpoints) as a starting point — see AGENTS.md for the rename flow to turn
it into your own resource.

## Prerequisites

- **Go {{.GoVersion}}+**
- **`de`** — the devedge build authority. It installs and pins the buf CLI + codegen plugins
  for you, so there is nothing else to put on PATH. `de generate` / `de build` / `de test` own
  the build; the `Makefile` reads `.devedge/make/devedge.mk` (written by `de sync`) and
  delegates to `de`, so `make ...` works too. (You already have `de` — you ran `de project init`.)
- **devedge** running locally (`de cluster start` if not already up)

## Development loop

```sh
# 1. Regenerate gRPC + gateway code after editing the proto (buf + pinned plugins).
#    internal/gen/ is generated — run this first on a fresh clone.
de generate

# 2. Bring up the service (postgres dependency included)
de project up

# 3. Run the server
make run

# 4. Exercise the REST API (see below)
```

## REST API examples

The gateway is reachable at `https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}` — the edge routes
`{{.APIPath}}` on `{{.Host}}` to this service and strips the prefix, so the
public URL is {{.Layout}} (`https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/...`) while the
service keeps serving `/v1/...`. A second service scaffolded under a different
`{{.APIPrefix}}/<domain>` shares this host without colliding.

Requests carry an optional subject header `Grpc-Metadata-x-dev-subject`.
The default subject (`dev`) is granted all permissions. Any other subject
is denied by the dev authorizer unless you extend the policy.

```sh
# Create
curl -s -X POST https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"url":"https://example.com/hook","secret":"s3cr3t","event_filters":["created","deleted"]}'

# List
curl -s https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints

# Get
curl -s https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints/{id}

# Update
curl -s -X PUT https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints/{endpoint.id} \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"{id}","url":"https://example.com/hook2","secret":"s3cr3t","event_filters":["created"]}'

# Delete
curl -s -X DELETE https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints/{id}

# Use a different subject (will be denied by default)
curl -s https://{{.Host}}{{.APIPath}}/v1/webhook-endpoints \
  -H "Grpc-Metadata-x-dev-subject: alice"
```

